    pisa: "Brazil scored 379 in PISA 2022, well below the OECD average. Brazil has improved from even lower scores in earlier cycles. Challenges include vast inequality between private and public schools, teacher shortages in rural areas, and high dropout rates. The system educates ~50 million students across enormously varied conditions.",
