    govEffectiveness: "56th percentile reflects a paradox: India has highly capable institutions (IITs, ISRO, Supreme Court, Election Commission) alongside significant bureaucratic challenges, corruption at lower levels, poor service delivery in rural areas, and gaps between policy and implementation.",
